### What I built
Introductory surface body using the Patch and Loft tools — a curved surface panel to explore how surface modelling differs from solid body workflows.

### Techniques used
- Patch tool to fill open edges
- Loft across non-parallel profiles
- Stitch tool to convert surface to solid
- Thicken command

### Key rules learned
- Surfaces have no volume — they are infinitely thin until thickened or stitched
- Every open edge must be closed before stitching to solid
- Surface bodies and solid bodies live in separate containers in the browser

### Time taken
~45 min

### Files
- `day11-surface-intro.f3d`
- `isometric.png`
